text.text:
I don't usually leave such long reviews, but this place is probably my favorite place in San Diego County.

My wife and I have been to Jeff's Burgers only half a dozen times and it's always feels like such a special occasion (only because we don't live very close by). If we lived in the area I swear this would be my weekend tradition. The menu is simple, but not boring. The staff is working their butts off, but still always so friendly. And the food is always a knock out of the park.

On our most recent visit, October 19 2024, it was a fairly busy time of day. Late lunch, around 2:30pm. Every seat was taken and there was a line out the door, but no one was impatient, these burgers are known to be worth the wait. The woman at the register (who I learned later was the General Manager, Marina) was helping the little boy in front of us decide how he liked his burger. With or without onions? pickles? etc. She was never pushy and let him take his time figuring out how he liked his food. She cared, in a way that was so loving, to make sure he was going to have a meal he enjoyed. With every interaction she prioritized the customer's experience of the establishment and the food over everything else. In between customers she assured everyone waiting in line that she appreciated our patience and that she would help us soon. When it was time to take our order she was the sweetest thing.

When she asked for my name so that they could call it out when our order was ready she had a great reaction to me saying "Jeff", because of the likeness to the restaurant's name. We all agreed that she should take my wife's name (Selina) down instead because it was more fun to say. She even spelled it right on the first try, which is uncommon, and she credited it to French being her native language and that is how it is commonly spelled in French.

We got seated outside on their little patio, which is small but cute. I will say that initially their seating area can seem cramped and leave you wishing for a little more elbow room, but I have found that it forces you to interact with the folks sitting around you in a way that feels kind of nice. When you are sitting outside, in a beach town, under a pink umbrella, and you need to ask your neighbor to excuse you are you squeeze by with a chocolate milkshake in one hand and a box of burgers in the next, no one can be grumpy or upset. Every single customer here is always in a good mood, and it is noticeable.
This place is just pure joy.

When my wife's name was called out the Manager handed my our food and I insisted on getting her name. Her name is Marina Zablit. When I met her I assumed she must own the place based on the love and care she was putting in to every action and word that came out of her mouth.
I don't know is she is a mother, but she has that community "mom" energy that just makes you feel at home.

This restaurant cooks all of the orders on one flat top grill, and everything is cooked to order with perfection. Their burgers come out hot and ready. Their milkshakes are real home-made milkshakes, like you dream about from when you were a kid. The fries are real, none of that frozen processed junk that doesn't even taste like a potato anymore.

I am leaving such a long review because I know what it is like to watch a little town lose it's soul to big business. I am a third generation Encinitas beach town local. My family moved here in the early 1940s. My family has watched these local towns lose their little Mom and Pop shops, and lose their very soul to corporations tourism.

But somehow, places like Jeff's Burgers and nestled in there still. Still keeping the local soul alive. Still cranking out the best this town has to offer.
It's not just food, it is the whole package.

I am counting the days until my next visit, and you best believe I will have a smile on my face the whole time I am here.

To close this long winded review out, I want to say great job, Jeffrey and JJ. From one Jeff to another, you are crushing it.

text.text:
Stopped by Sushi Nekosan for dinner with a friend to try a few rolls. The menu has a bunch of fun and creative roll options. Got the Special Hawaiian, the Baja Lemon Cilantro and a sushi/avocado. I loved the Special Hawaiian the most, it had all my favorites. The fish was super fresh and they were not skimpy with the portions.

My friend got the small sake ($6) and while I don't like sake, I definitely want to mention it because I felt the amount she got for the price was very generous.

Service was good, our waiter was very attentive and patient with questions we had about the menu.

I'd come back if I happened to be in the area because I know the sushi rolls will be of good quality, but it probably won't be one of my go-tos.

It took almost 40 minutes for mine and my mothers food to arrive and all we got was one roll and a couple pieces of nigiri. They also completely forgot about the hand roll I ordered (brought 20 minutes after the rest of the food). See attached image, this is not what a spicy tuna should look like. It was almost light orange and flavorless. It is ridiculously overpriced for the quality, 6$ for miso soup, and 25$ rolls. All the fish was medicore at best with my salmon hardly even having color.  If you want a much better meal try Sushi Ota or Sushi Mori.

text.text: I like eating sushi always. And what I love more is that different places making different rolls. Even the same type of rolls, different chefs make them slightly different. I love that. This place definitely has a very unique roll we never saw before - Samurai Roll which has a tons of red onion on the top. It’s really interesting. I mean if you like red onion, you will like it. But for me, I don’t eat raw onion so I couldn’t enjoy it. I really like my Girls Night roll. And their vegetables tempura is delicious, it’s not on the menu tho, you can ask for it. Anyways, if you work or live nearby, here is not bad at all to have lunch and dinner.

Our first time dining here. Didn’t have reservation but we were seated right away.

Food: 4/5
-Green Aqua $21- melted in your mouth.
-Caterpillar $16- yummy!
-Spicy Scallop $9- couldn’t taste the scallops.
-Gentleman $17- just ok.
-Unagi $9.50- loved the eel sauce.
Tonkotsu $15- creamy delicious!

Drinks:
Hot Sake $7
Beer $8

Service:
Fast. They brought everything we asked for. Nice touch, the bot delivered our food to the table.

text.text: Open later than most, Great portions, good service, delicious Sushi.

originalText.text: Open later than most, Great portions, good service, delicious Sushi.

text.text: A true locals gem. The rating on this place should be much higher than what it is. I have lived all over the country and this is still one of the best sushi places I’ve ever been to. The rice is phenomenal, the proportion of ingredients is always perfect, and the portions of the roll are really generous. Despite being around for many years, their pricing has remained reasonable and every time I’m in the area I try to order from here. I guarantee if you give this place a try it will not be your last time ordering from them.

text.text: I came in yesterday with my grandma for lunch, it was a busy time for Jeffs’, but the owner (I think) Marina made the wait pleasant and was so welcoming when we walked in. I ordered the El Jefe and a side of onion rings with a vanilla shake. The food was so good, and what made the experience even better was the top tier customer service we experienced from Marina. She made conversation with my grandma in Arabic and in French and made her whole day after that. Next time my grandma’s in town she’s already asked that our first stop be Jeffs’ Beach Burgers.

text.text:
Stopped by Sushi Nekosan for dinner with a friend to try a few rolls. The menu has a bunch of fun and creative roll options. Got the Special Hawaiian, the Baja Lemon Cilantro and a sushi/avocado. I loved the Special Hawaiian the most, it had all my favorites. The fish was super fresh and they were not skimpy with the portions.

My friend got the small sake ($6) and while I don't like sake, I definitely want to mention it because I felt the amount she got for the price was very generous.

Service was good, our waiter was very attentive and patient with questions we had about the menu.

I'd come back if I happened to be in the area because I know the sushi rolls will be of good quality, but it probably won't be one of my go-tos.
